.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354656399551134FF36FDD2FF00FD15" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF136E899551134FF36FDD2FF00FD15" blockId="84.[124,653,193,715]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B99551134FDE8FDD2FD3FFDAD" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[583,652,604,627]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA99551134FDE8FDD2FD3FFDAD" box="[583,652,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">panus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(patch) is a Latin noun which refers to the loose aggregate of white setae on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
